<p>
  She brought music, discipline, and creativity into our home, and she
  modeled a quiet strength that shaped both family life and my own sense
  of responsibility and care for others.
</p>

<h3>My Father</h3>

<p>
  My father was born in Port Arthur, Texas, in 1939. He began his career
  in commercial construction as a superintendent and worked his way up
  through experience and leadership to become Vice President at
  Mayfield Construction in Houston.
</p>

<figure>
  <img src="/images/dadprofiles.jpg" alt="Dad Profile Picture RM Mayfield" />
  <figcaption>
    Dad's profile picture from RM Mayfield Construction, reflecting his legacy role in the commercial construction industry.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<p>
  He was responsible for the delivery of multiple multistory multi-million dollar office buildings
  across Houston. His crown achievement was serving as General Superintendent
  for the Marriott RiverCenter Hotel, a project that reflected both the scale
  of his responsibility and the trust placed in his leadership.
</p>

<figure>
  <img src="/images/marriottrc.jpg" alt="Marriott RiverCenter Hotel" />
